The paper focuses on deep latent variable models for text generation, which is a topic closely related to natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach to address the "posterior collapse" issue in VAEs, which is a common problem in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper applies the proposed models to various text generation scenarios, including language modeling, style transfer, and dialog response generation, which involve different aspects of computer vision (CV) and NLP. Therefore, cs.NE and cs.CV are also possible sub-categories.
